hm2UserConfigTable.name: hm2UserConfigTable
hm2UserConfigTable.description: User configuration table. This table provides the functionality the system uses for any interaction started by the user - authentication, encryption - changing authentication, password and access role for login purposes through Web, CLI, SSH, SNMPv3. For SNMPv3 the standard SNMPv3 authentication/encryption methods are used. To create a new user set hm2UserStatus to 'createAndWait, and set the corresponding objects to their values. Setting hm2UserStatus to 'active' activates the user. To delete a user, set hm2UserStatus to 'destroy'. Creating a new user in the hm2UserConfigTable always creates a new user in the SNMPv3 tables. The newly created SNMPv3 user will get the corresponding view in the SNMPv3 tables which matches to one of the given roles the user can have. All objects in this table can be set while a row is 'active'.

hm2UserPassword.name: hm2UserPassword
hm2UserPassword.description: Agent user password This object will always return '********' when read. The minimum size of the password is defined with the hm2PwdMgmtMinLength object. The user password can be set while the row is active.

hm2UserAccessRole.name: hm2UserAccessRole
hm2UserAccessRole.description: Agent user's role. The user's role can be set while the row is active.

hm2UserLockoutStatus.name: hm2UserLockoutStatus
hm2UserLockoutStatus.description: Displays whether the user account is locked due to excessive failed login attempts. If the user is locked out, the hm2UserLockoutStatus status is 'true'. Only a user with the administrator role can set this status back to 'false'.

hm2UserPwdChangePerm.name: hm2UserPwdChangePerm
hm2UserPwdChangePerm.description: Displays whether the user is allowed to change his own password. Only a user with the administrator role can set this value.

hm2UserPwdPolicyChk.name: hm2UserPwdPolicyChk
hm2UserPwdPolicyChk.description: Displays whether the password policy check is enabled or not. The password policy check objects are defined in the hm2PwdMgmtGroup. Even if this object if set to 'disable' the size of a new password has to be at least the size of the hm2PwdMgmtMinLength object set. Only a user with the administrator role can set this value.

hm2UserSnmpAuthType.name: hm2UserSnmpAuthType
hm2UserSnmpAuthType.description: SNMPv3 user authentication. The user password must be set to a string greater than or equal to 8 characters for this to be set to anything but none(0). - hmacmd5(1) -> Use HMAC-MD5 authentication - hmacsha(2) -> Use HMAC-SHA authentication The user authentication type can be set while the row is active .

hm2UserSnmpEncType.name: hm2UserSnmpEncType
hm2UserSnmpEncType.description: SNMPv3 user encryption Can not be set to des(2) or aesCfb128(3) if hm2UserSnmpAuthenticationType is set to none(0). - none(0) -> no encryption used - des(1) -> DES encryption used - aesCfb128(2) -> AES-128 encryption used The user encryption type can be set while the row is active.

hm2UserStatus.name: hm2UserStatus
hm2UserStatus.description: Agent user status. active(1) - This user account is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this user account.

hm2UserLastUserCreated.name: hm2UserLastUserCreated
hm2UserLastUserCreated.description: Name of the last user created in hm2UserConfigTable.

hm2UserLastUserDeleted.name: hm2UserLastUserDeleted
hm2UserLastUserDeleted.description: Name of the last user deleted in hm2UserConfigTable.

hm2UserCustomAccessRole2NameTable.name: hm2UserCustomAccessRole2NameTable
hm2UserCustomAccessRole2NameTable.description: Custom based role to name mapping.

hm2UserCustomAccessRoleStatus.name: hm2UserCustomAccessRoleStatus
hm2UserCustomAccessRoleStatus.description: Custom-based role to name command row status. active(1) - This user account is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this role to name entry.

hm2UserCustomCliCmdInheritTable.name: hm2UserCustomCliCmdInheritTable
hm2UserCustomCliCmdInheritTable.description: Base access role from which the custom-based CLI commands are inherited from.

hm2UserCustomCliBaseAccessRole.name: hm2UserCustomCliBaseAccessRole

hm2UserCustomCliBaseAccessRoleStatus.name: hm2UserCustomCliBaseAccessRoleStatus
hm2UserCustomCliBaseAccessRoleStatus.description: Custom-based CLI base access role command row status. active(1) - This user account is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this role to name entry.

hm2UserCustomCliCmdTable.name: hm2UserCustomCliCmdTable
hm2UserCustomCliCmdTable.description: Table containing the custom-based CLI commands.

hm2UserCustomCliIndex.name: hm2UserCustomCliIndex
hm2UserCustomCliIndex.description: Index of the custom based CLI commands.

hm2UserCustomCliCommand.name: hm2UserCustomCliCommand
hm2UserCustomCliCommand.description: The custom based CLI command to be assigned.

hm2UserCustomCliType.name: hm2UserCustomCliType
hm2UserCustomCliType.description: The custom based CLI command to be included or excluded in respect to the base role.

hm2UserCustomCliStatus.name: hm2UserCustomCliStatus
hm2UserCustomCliStatus.description: Custom-based CLI command row status. active(1) - This user account is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this CLI command entry.

hm2PwdMgmtMinLength.name: hm2PwdMgmtMinLength
hm2PwdMgmtMinLength.description: Minimum length for user passwords All new local user passwords must be at least this many characters in length.

hm2PwdMgmtLoginAttempts.name: hm2PwdMgmtLoginAttempts
hm2PwdMgmtLoginAttempts.description: The number of allowable failed local authentication attempts before the user's account is locked. A value of '0' indicates that user accounts will never be locked.

hm2PwdMgmtMinUpperCase.name: hm2PwdMgmtMinUpperCase
hm2PwdMgmtMinUpperCase.description: The number of minimum allowable uppercase letters in a password. Minimum of '0' means no restriction on that set of characters.

hm2PwdMgmtMinLowerCase.name: hm2PwdMgmtMinLowerCase
hm2PwdMgmtMinLowerCase.description: The number of minimum allowable lowercase letters in a password. Minimum of '0' means no restriction on that set of characters.

hm2PwdMgmtMinNumericNumbers.name: hm2PwdMgmtMinNumericNumbers
hm2PwdMgmtMinNumericNumbers.description: The number of minimum allowable numeric numbers in a password. Minimum of '0' means no restriction on that set of characters.

hm2PwdMgmtMinSpecialCharacters.name: hm2PwdMgmtMinSpecialCharacters
hm2PwdMgmtMinSpecialCharacters.description: The number of minimum allowable special characters in a password. Minimum of '0' means no restriction on that set of characters. The following special characters are allowed: !#$%&'()*+,-./:;<=>?@[\\]^_`{}~

hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdActive.name: hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdActive
hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdActive.description: Shows if one or more default passwords are active for users configured in the hm2UserConfigTable. The hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusTable shows for which users the default password is currently actice.

hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusTable.name: hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusTable
hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusTable.description: Table showing for which users defined in hm2UserConfigTable the default password has not been changed.

hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusUserName.name: hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusUserName
hm2PwdMgmtDefaultPwdStatusUserName.description: The name of the default user for which the default password has not been changed.

hm2UserApplicationListTable.name: hm2UserApplicationListTable
hm2UserApplicationListTable.description: This table provides the functionality the system uses to assign an authentication list to an application. All objects in this table can be set while a row is 'active'.

hm2UserApplicationListAuthListName.name: hm2UserApplicationListAuthListName
hm2UserApplicationListAuthListName.description: The authentication list used for this application to authenticate to the system. The application authentication list can be set while the row is active.

hm2UserApplicationListStatus.name: hm2UserApplicationListStatus
hm2UserApplicationListStatus.description: Application row status. active(1) - This user account is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this application list entry.

hm2UserAuthListTable.name: hm2UserAuthListTable
hm2UserAuthListTable.description: The hm2UserAuthListTable holds up to 5 policies a user authenticates to the system.

hm2UserAuthListName.name: hm2UserAuthListName
hm2UserAuthListName.description: Authentication list index. Unique name used for indexing into this table.

hm2UserAuthListPolicy1.name: hm2UserAuthListPolicy1
hm2UserAuthListPolicy1.description: Authentication list policy 1. Configures the first authentication policy to use when this list is specified. - local -> authentication is done through local user database - radius -> authentication is done through a RADIUS server - ias -> authentication is done through a (i)ntegrated (a)uthentication (s)erver - cam -> authentication is done through a CAM server (via LDAP) - ldap -> authentication is done through a AD server (via LDAP) - reject -> authentication is rejected/not allowed. Note: If a policy is set to 'reject' further policies are ignored.

hm2UserAuthListStatus.name: hm2UserAuthListStatus
hm2UserAuthListStatus.description: The status of the authentication list. active(1) - This entry is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this authentication list.

hm2UserIasUserPassword.name: hm2UserIasUserPassword
hm2UserIasUserPassword.description: The (I)ntegrated (A)uthentication (S)erver user password. This object will always return '********' when read. The user password can be set while the row is active.

hm2UserIasUserStatus.name: hm2UserIasUserStatus
hm2UserIasUserStatus.description: The status of the IAS users. active(1) - This entry is active. notInService(2) - Row has been suspended. notReady(3) - Row has incomplete values. createAndGo(4) - Accept row values and activate. createAndWait(5) - Accept row values and wait. destroy(6) - Set to this value to remove this IAS entry.

hm2UserCreatedTrap.name: hm2UserCreatedTrap
hm2UserCreatedTrap.description: This notification is send when a new user is added to the hm2UserConfigTable.

hm2UserDeletedTrap.name: hm2UserDeletedTrap
hm2UserDeletedTrap.description: This notification is send when a user is deleted from the hm2UserConfigTable.

hm2UserLockedTrap.name: hm2UserLockedTrap
hm2UserLockedTrap.description: This notification is send when a user is locked due to excessive failed login attempts.

hm2UserPwdChangedTrap.name: hm2UserPwdChangedTrap
hm2UserPwdChangedTrap.description: This notification is send when a password for a user is changed.

hm2UserPwdPolicyChkChangedTrap.name: hm2UserPwdPolicyChkChangedTrap
hm2UserPwdPolicyChkChangedTrap.description: This notification is send when the password policy for a user is changed.

hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESLenCharset.name: hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESLenCharset
hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESLenCharset.description: Indicates that the chosen entry name uses not allowed character(s). Allowed are alphanumerical characters and name size from 1 to 32.

hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESPwdLenCharset.name: hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESPwdLenCharset
hm2UserMgmtGlobalSESPwdLenCharset.description: Indicates that the chosen password is incorrect. Check character set, length, policy matching (if password policy checker is enabled).

hm2UserMgmtUserSESActivate.name: hm2UserMgmtUserSESActivate
hm2UserMgmtUserSESActivate.description: Indicates that the chosen user entry can not be activated. Be sure that a user password has been successfully set before.

hm2UserMgmtUserSESDeactivate.name: hm2UserMgmtUserSESDeactivate
hm2UserMgmtUserSESDeactivate.description: Indicates that the chosen user entry can not be deactivated. Be sure that this user is not the last active admin on the device.

hm2UserMgmtApplSESAddDel.name: hm2UserMgmtApplSESAddDel
hm2UserMgmtApplSESAddDel.description: Indicates that the chosen entry can not be added or deleted. Notice that application lists can neither be added nor deleted.

hm2UserMgmtApplSESDeactivate.name: hm2UserMgmtApplSESDeactivate
hm2UserMgmtApplSESDeactivate.description: Indicates that the chosen entry can not be deactivated. Be sure that this list is not referenced to an authentication list (hm2UserApplicationListAuthListName has to be set to a zero length string).

hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDuplPolicy.name: hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDuplPolicy
hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDuplPolicy.description: Indicates that the chosen policy of this entry can not be set twice. Be sure that a policy is set only once per authentication list (exception: the policy 'reject' can be set several times).

hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDeactivate.name: hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDeactivate
hm2UserMgmtAuthSESDeactivate.description: Indicates that the chosen entry can not be deactivated. Be sure that this list is not referenced by an apllication list (hm2UserApplicationListAuthListName is not set to this authentication list name).
